Koppers Holdings Inc. Koppers H (NYSE:KOP):
Koppers Holdings Inc. Schedules Second Quarter 2017 Conference Call. 
 The company is now down by -1.98% since yesterday’s close of $37.95. 
 Koppers Holdings Inc., launched on November 12, 2004, is a global integrated provider of treated wood products, wood treatment chemicals and carbon compounds. The Company operates through three segments: Railroad and Utility Products and Services (RUPS), Carbon Materials and Chemicals (CMC) and Performance Chemicals (PC). The Business’s products and services are used in a range of markets, including the railroad, specialty chemical, utility, residential lumber, agriculture, aluminum, steel, rubber and construction industries. The Business’s manufacturing facilities are located in North America, South America, Australasia, China and Europe..         Advertisement






 Shares are trading at $37.20 which is just over $35.88, the stock’s 50 day moving average and just a bit lower than the 200 day moving average of $39.90.  The 50 day moving average went up by +3.68% and the 200 day average was down $-2.70. 
 Koppers Holdings Inc. Koppers H’s P/E ratio is 22.86 and market cap is 773.98M.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $1.63 and is projected to be $2.92 for the current year with 20,806,000 shares presently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $0.90 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $3.32. 
 A few brokerage analysts have released opinions on Koppers Holdings Inc. Koppers H.   On June 28 the stock rating was upgraded to “Buy” from “Hold” in a report from Wunderlich. On May 31 the company was downgraded from “Buy” to “Hold” in a report issued by Jefferies.
 On November 29 the stock rating was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” in a statement from Wunderlich. On July 18 the company was downgraded from “Buy” to “Neutral” by analysts at Monness Crespi Hardt.
 Barrington Research started coverage setting a rating of “Outperform” and a price target of $39.00. On March 14 the company was rated “Buy” by Monness Crespi Hardt a boost from the previous “Neutral” rating.
