(KOP) Shares Trading down at $37.20 Koppers Holdings Inc. Schedules Second…
July 21, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Koppers Holdings Inc. Koppers H (NYSE:KOP):
Koppers Holdings Inc. Schedules Second Quarter 2017 Conference Call. 
 The company is now down since yesterday’s close of $37.95. 
 Koppers Holdings Inc., launched on November 12, 2004, is a global integrated provider of treated wood products, wood treatment chemicals and carbon compounds. The Company operates through three segments: Railroad and Utility Products and Services (RUPS), Carbon Materials and Chemicals (CMC) and Performance Chemicals (PC). The Business’s products and services are used in a range of markets, including the railroad, specialty chemical, utility, residential lumber, agriculture, aluminum, steel, rubber and construction industries. The Business’s manufacturing facilities are located in North America, South America, Australasia, China and Europe.. 
 It is trading at $37.20 a tad above $35.88, the 50 day moving average and a tad under the 200 day moving average of $39.90.  The 50 day moving average was up by +3.68% and the 200 day average went down by -6.77%. 





 The P/E ratio is currently 22.86 and the market value is 773.98M.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $1.63 and is estimated to be $2.92 for the current year with 20,806,000 shares outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $0.90 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $3.32. 
 A few brokerage firms have released opinions on Koppers Holdings Inc. Koppers H.   On June 28, 2017 the stock rating was set at “Buy” according to a Wunderlich report which was a boost from the previous “Hold” rating. On May 31 the company was rated “Hold” by Jefferies a cut from the previous “Buy” rating.
 On November 29, 2016 the stock rating was changed to a “Hold” in a report from Wunderlich down from the previous “Buy” rating. On July 18 the stock rating was downgraded to “Neutral” from “Buy” in a statement from Monness Crespi Hardt.
 On June 8 analysts at Barrington Research issued its first research report on the stock setting a rating of “Outperform” and setting a price target of $39.00. On March 14 the company was upgraded from “Neutral” to “Buy” by analysts at Monness Crespi Hardt.






